Reasoning: The paper deals with the achievable rates and decoding complexity of LDPC codes over parallel channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers memoryless, binary-input, and output-symmetric (MBIOS) channels, which falls under the category of network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of LDPC-coded modulation, which is related to communication and coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also touches upon the topic of punctured LDPC codes, which is related to signal processing and communications (cs.SI) as well as multimedia (cs.MM).
